nodes.text: This individual was the mother of Nakari Kelen and the wife of Fayet Kelen, and was a member of the band named Hakko Drazlip and the Tootle Froots. She wrote a song titled "Vader's Many Prosthetic Parts" that satirized Darth Vader. As a result, she was sent to the spice mines of Kessel by the Galactic Empire, along with the members of the band, and presumed dead by her daughter.
